### Version   
2.5.16
### Reproduction link   
https://jsfiddle.net/hLinx/eywraw8t/280913/
### Steps to reproduce   
1. Register a component , by directive or methods to change `this.$el.parentNode`
2. Put the component behind the v-for list
```
<template>
  <div>
    <div v-for="item in arr">{{item}}</div>
    <com />
  </div>
</template>
```
### What is actually happening?
````
function insert (parent, elm, ref) {
    if (isDef(parent)) {
      if (isDef(ref)) {
        // ref.parentNode has been changed，insertBefore can't execute.
        if (ref.parentNode === parent) {
          nodeOps.insertBefore(parent, elm, ref)
        }
      } else {
        nodeOps.appendChild(parent, elm)
      }
    }
  }
``

### What problem does this feature solve?
```javascript
const clickObj = {
  click() {
    console.log(this) // this will be null or window, depent on the environment.
  }
}

new Vue({
  el: '#app',
  data() {
    return {
      clickObj,
    }
  },
  template: `<div v-on="{clickObj}">unbind this</div>`
})
```
Maybe it is better to bind `this` in `v-on` directive, so developer can get Vue instance without bind `this` themselves.

### What does the proposed API look like?
Auto bind  `this` in `v-on` directive

