### Version
3.0.1

### Reproduction link
[https://github.com/ffxsam/repro-mapstate-bug](https://github.com/ffxsam/repro-mapstate-bug)

### Steps to reproduce
1. Clone repo
1. Run yarn
1. Open src/components/HelloWorld.vue

### What is expected?
There should be no type errors

### What is actually happening?
There is a type error on line 52

---

If you comment out lines 46-48 (the `fake` computed property), the type error on line 52 goes away. It seems `mapState` and `mapGetters` merges in an interface property, `[x: string] => any` whenever they're used. But if other computed properties are added, this fails to exist.

For instance, with lines 46-48 _not_ commented out, I mouse over `this` in the method, and I see this:

```
{
    doit(): void;
} & {
    fake: string;
} & Readonly<{
    msg: string;
}> & Vue
```

However, if I comment out lines 46-48, hovering over `this` reveals:

```
{
    doit(): void;
} & {
    [x: string]: any;
} & Readonly<{
    msg: string;
}> & Vue
```

